    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>010410</citedRange></bibl>.</p>           
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="χῶρος"><expan><abbr>χῶρο</abbr><ex>ς</ex></expan></w> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φίλων"><expan><abbr>Φίλων</abbr><ex>ος</ex></expan></name></persName> 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                    <p>
                        <app loc="1"><rdg resp="#robinson1913 #fraser-matthews1987"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66178"><name>Χωροφίλω</name></persName></rdg></app>
                    </p>           
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Emplacement de Philon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Place of Philon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Posto di Philon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>مكان فيلون (أي هنا دفن فيلون).</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The queer name <foreign xml:lang="grc">*Χωρόφιλος</foreign> admitted by Robinson, has been registered in <bibl><ptr target="#fraser-matthews1987"/></bibl>.
                    In fact, between omicron and chi there is a slight shift, allowing the proposed abbreviation.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
